    "body": "The problem is - we try to check only One language - German. But it starts to check English text too.\n\nWith 'ru-RU'  everything works fine - webFrame.setSpellCheckProvider underlines wrong russian words and doesn't underlined English words at all:\n\n```\nwebFrame.setSpellCheckProvider('ru-RU', true, {spellCheck: function (text) {\n    //this code is performed only when user input text in Russian, when Eng - no  \n    return !customSpellChecker.isMisspelled(text);\n}});\n```\n\nSo I guess the issue is not in custom spell-check provider, but in webFrame.setSpellCheckProvider.\n"
  },
